  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Shahrukh khan movies?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has delivered numerous iconic performances over his illustrious career. Here are some of his best and most beloved movies, known for their storytelling, acting, and cultural impact:\n\n### 1. **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)**  \n   - A timeless romantic drama that redefined Bollywood romance. It\u2019s one of the longest-running films in Indian cinema history.\n\n### 2. **Kal Ho Naa Ho (2003)**  \n   - A heartwarming and emotional story about love, friendship, and life. SRK's performance is both charming and tear-jerking.\n\n### 3. **Swades (2004)**  \n   - A critically acclaimed film where SRK plays an NRI returning to India to bring change. It\u2019s a deeply moving and inspiring story.\n\n### 4. **Chak De! India (2007)**  \n   - A sports drama where SRK plays a disgraced hockey coach leading the Indian women\u2019s team to victory. It\u2019s a motivational and patriotic film.\n\n### 5. **My Name is Khan (2010)**  \n   - A touching story of a man with Asperger\u2019s syndrome on a journey to meet the U.S. President. It addresses themes of love, discrimination, and resilience.\n\n### 6. **Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham (2001)**  \n   - A family drama with a stellar cast, blending emotions, romance, and drama. SRK\u2019s role as Rahul remains iconic.\n\n### 7. **Devdas (2002)**  \n   - A visually stunning tragic romance based on the classic novel. SRK\u2019s portrayal of the doomed lover is unforgettable.\n\n### 8. **Dil Se.. (1998)**  \n   - A romantic thriller with a unique narrative and soulful music. SRK\u2019s intense performance stands out.\n\n### 9. **Kabhi Haan Kabhi Naa (1994)**  \n   - A coming-of-age story where SRK plays a charming yet flawed character. It\u2019s a fan favorite for its relatability.\n\n### 10. **Om Shanti Om (2007)**  \n   - A blend of romance, drama, and reincarnation with a meta take on Bollywood. SRK\u2019s double role is highly entertaining.\n\n### 11. **Baazigar (1993)**  \n   - A dark thriller where SRK plays an anti-hero, marking a turning point in his career.\n\n### 12. **Veer-Zaara (2004)**  \n   - A cross-border love story that\u2019s both poetic and emotionally resonant.\n\n### 13. **Chennai Express (2013)**  \n   - A masala entertainer with SRK in a comedic role, blending romance and action.\n\n### 14. **Raees (2017)**  \n   - A gritty gangster drama where SRK delivers a powerful performance as a bootlegger.\n\n### 15. **Don (2006) and Don 2 (2011)**  \n   - SRK\u2019s portrayal of the suave and dangerous Don is iconic, blending action and style.\n\nThese movies showcase Shah Rukh Khan\u2019s versatility as an actor, from romantic roles to intense dramas and thrillers. His charisma and acting prowess have made him a global icon.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
